<h1 id="problem-building-a-number-guess-game-with-html-and-javascript">Problem: Building a Number Guess Game with HTML and JavaScript</h1>
<h2 id="objectives">Objectives:</h2>
<ul>
<li>Understand the basic structure of HTML and JavaScript.</li>
<li>Learn how to create interactive elements using JavaScript.</li>
<li>Develop a simple game logic to guess a random number.</li>
<li>Implement user input and feedback mechanisms.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="tasks">Tasks:</h2>
<h3 id="task-1-html-structure">Task 1: HTML Structure</h3>
<ul>
<li>Create a basic HTML structure with a <code>div</code> element to contain the game elements.</li>
<li>Add a <code>h1</code> element to display the game title.</li>
<li>Create a <code>p</code> element to display instructions or messages.</li>
<li>Add an <code>input</code> element to allow the user to enter their guess.</li>
<li>Add a <code>button</code> element to submit the guess.</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="task-2-javascript-logic">Task 2: JavaScript Logic</h3>
<ul>
<li>Random Number Generation:
<ul>
<li>Use JavaScript's <code>Math.random()</code> function to generate a random number within a specified range.</li>
<li>Store the generated number in a variable.</li>
</ul></li>
<li>User Input:
<ul>
<li>Use the <code>getElementById()</code> method to access the input element.</li>
<li>Get the value entered by the user and store it in a variable.</li>
</ul></li>
<li>Game Logic:
<ul>
<li>Compare the user's guess with the generated number.</li>
<li>If the guess is correct, display a message indicating a win and the number of attempts.</li>
<li>If the guess is incorrect, provide feedback (e.g., "Too high" or "Too low") and allow the user to try again.</li>
</ul></li>
<li>Attempt Counter:
<ul>
<li>Implement a counter to track the number of attempts made by the user.</li>
<li>Update the counter after each guess.</li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<h3 id="task-3-user-interface">Task 3: User Interface</h3>
<ul>
<li>Feedback Display:
<ul>
<li>Use the textContent property to update the p element with feedback messages.</li>
<li>Display appropriate messages based on the user's guess.</li>
</ul></li>
<li>Game Over:
<ul>
<li>Once the user guesses the correct number, display a message indicating the game is over and the total number of attempts.</li>
<li>Optionally, provide a way to restart the game.</li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<h3 id="task-4-testing-and-refinement">Task 4: Testing and Refinement</h3>
<ul>
<li>Test the game thoroughly to ensure it functions correctly.</li>
<li>Address any bugs or issues that arise.</li>
<li>Consider adding additional features or improvements, such as:
<ul>
<li>Difficulty levels</li>
<li>Time limits</li>
<li>High scores</li>
<li>Custom number ranges</li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<p>By completing these tasks, you will have successfully built a functional number guess game using HTML and JavaScript.</p>
